{
  "text": "Game 1: Suppose TPA already has a valid auditing proof P = {γ , C, σ } from CSP based on the auditing challenge Q = {c, r, k ψ , k π }, then P = {γ , C, σ } must satisfy the verification equation [CITATION_1] . Suppose some DOs' data files have been corrupted, the malicious CSP will forge an auditing proofP = {γ ,Ĉ, σ } on the incorrect data files according to the auditing challenge Q = {c, r, k ψ , k π }. The CSP will win the Game 1 if the forged auditing proofP can pass the TPA's verification. Otherwise, the CSP fails. We will prove that if the CSP can win the Game 1, the TPA can solve an arbitrary DLP instance.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "44085007"
